<subSubSection lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[166,696,1414,1731]" lastBlockId="26.[742,1271,1414,1731]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
COMMENTS: A potential larval character for the 
<taxonomicName box="[259,417,1620,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Augochlorini">Augochlorini</taxonomicName>
is the development of the mandibular cusp into an acute, elongate projection (McGinley, 1981). Larvae, however, are known for only a few, scattered genera (table 2) and until further work on augochlorine immatures is undertaken, the validity of this character in supporting the monophyly of the tribe remains uncertain.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[742,1271,1414,1731]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Authorship of the tribe has universally been given to Moure (1943a). In actuality Beebe (1925), in a semipopular treatment of the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[917,1010,1620,1643]" name="Guyana" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, mentions the name ‘‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beebe" authorityYear="1925" box="[760,933,1649,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Augochloridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Augochloridae</taxonomicName>
’’ to include tropical species of the genera 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Engel" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[914,1051,1679,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[914,1051,1679,1702]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Augochlora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1115,1213,1679,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1115,1213,1679,1702]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Halictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
